## 5. License Verification and Activation

**(a)** The Software requires a valid License Key and successful device registration for operation. The Software will not function without completed license verification.

**(b)** The Software communicates with Licensor's servers to:

  - Verify the validity and status of the License Key.
  - Register, authenticate, and fingerprint the Device.
  - Download updated Detection Assets and model weights.
  - Transmit anonymous, aggregate usage statistics (scan counts, detection counts).

**(c)** Licensee acknowledges that persistent or periodic network connectivity to Licensor's servers is required for license verification and Detection Asset updates.

**(d)** Licensor reserves the right to revoke or suspend any License Key at any time if Licensor determines, in its sole discretion, that the terms of this Agreement have been violated.

---

## 6. Confidentiality

**(a)** Licensee acknowledges that the Software, its architecture, Detection Assets, performance characteristics, and all related technical information constitute **confidential and proprietary information** and **trade secrets** of Licensor.

**(b)** Licensee shall not disclose, publish, or make available to any third party any confidential information obtained through the use of the Software, including but not limited to: detection methodologies, model behavior, scan results containing internal metadata, or API responses revealing implementation details.

**(c)** This confidentiality obligation survives the termination of this Agreement and remains in effect indefinitely.

---

## 7. Data Collection and Privacy

**(a)** The Software may collect and transmit the following data to Licensor's servers:

  - Device identification information (hostname, UUID, system fingerprint).
  - License status and validation data.
  - Aggregate scan statistics (file counts, detection counts, scan durations).
  - SHA256 hashes of detected files (for threat intelligence purposes).

**(b)** The Software does **NOT** collect or transmit: file contents, file names (except hashes), personal data, user credentials, browsing history, or any data unrelated to its security monitoring function.

**(c)** All data processing is conducted in compliance with Regulation (EU) 2016/679 (General Data Protection Regulation — **GDPR**) and applicable Spanish data protection legislation (Ley Orgánica 3/2018 — **LOPDGDD**). See Licensor's Privacy Policy at [https://reqsock.com/privacy](https://reqsock.com/privacy) for full details, including data retention periods and data subject rights.

**(d)** Licensee is responsible for ensuring that its use of the Software complies with all applicable data protection regulations within Licensee's jurisdiction.

