## 13. Termination

**(a)** This Agreement is effective from the date of acceptance until terminated.

**(b)** Licensor may terminate this Agreement and revoke the License Key **immediately and without notice** if Licensee breaches any term hereof.

**(c)** Licensee may terminate this Agreement at any time by uninstalling the Software and destroying all copies. No refund shall be provided for the remaining license period.

**(d)** Upon termination, Licensee must:
  - Immediately cease all use of the Software, SDK, and Plugins.
  - Uninstall and delete all copies of the Software from all Devices.
  - Destroy all Detection Assets, documentation, and confidential materials.
  - Certify in writing, upon request, that all copies have been destroyed.

**(e)** The following sections survive termination: **3 (Restrictions), 4 (Intellectual Property), 6 (Confidentiality), 10 (Warranty Disclaimer), 11 (Limitation of Liability), 12 (Indemnification), and 14 (Governing Law).**

